'''Kosobudy''' {{IPAr|pl|k|o|s|o|'|b|u|d|y}} is a [[village]] in the administrative district of [[Gmina Bia<U+0142>y B<U+00F3>r]], within [[Szczecinek County]], [[West Pomeranian Voivodeship]], in north-western Poland.<ref name="TERYT">{{cite web |url=http://www.stat.gov.pl/broker/access/prefile/listPreFiles.jspa |title=Central Statistical Office (GUS) - TERYT (National Register of Territorial Land Apportionment Journal) |date=2008-06-01 |language=Polish}}</ref>

Before 1945 the area was part of [[Germany]]. For the history of the region, see [[History of Pomerania]].

